    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pots!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are starting to brown, reduce the heat to medium and add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>with<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> </strong>3/4 of your <strong>curry powder</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), your <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>sultanas</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and <strong>spinach</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add<strong> </strong>300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, top with your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-14 min or until all the water has absorbed, the rice is cooked and the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the pot from the heat and set aside for 3-4 min \u2013 this is your <strong>masala basa biryani</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the biryani is ready, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to a small heatproof bowl with your <strong>remaining curry powder</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>and cook for 20-30 secs or until the butter is melted</p><p>Once melted, add your <strong>mango chutney</strong> and mix until fully combined \u2013 this is your<strong> mango curry butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-masala-basa-biryani-with-yoghurt-and-curry-mango-butter/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>masala basa biryani </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Top with your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>then drizzle over the<strong> mango curry butter</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
